    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><img src="/images/Git-Logo-2Color.png" width="300" title="Git Logo" ></p>

<p>These are 3 aliases that i find myself using all the time, since they are used a lot they tend to shorten my workflow a little bit. I'm using the jQuery repo for examples.</p>

<h3>Short status</h3>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>git config --global alias.s "status -s"</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p><img class="center" src="/images/git_short.png" title="git s preview" ></p>

<p>Shortens git status, making it more readable and useful for a quick overview of staged and unstaged changes.</p>

<h3>One Line Log</h3>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>git config --global alias.ol "log --oneline"</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p><img class="center" src="/images/git_ol.png" title="git ol preview" ></p>

<p>Provides a quick overview of the recently done commits without the author and date. Good for finding a commit hash for a quick checkout.</p>

<h3>Quick branch and checkout</h3>

<p><div class='bogus-wrapper'><notextile><figure class='code'><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class=''><span class='line'>git config --global alias.b "checkout -b"</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure></notextile></div></p>

<p><img class="center" src="/images/git_branch.png" title="git b preview" ></p>

<p>Creates a new branch and instantly switches the newly created branch.</p>
]]></content>
